title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> be any <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0049.xml"
addr="nt-0049"
title="Cyclic Extension">cyclic extension</fr:link> of degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Assume <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {char}}\nolimits (\mathbb {F})\nmid  n]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> contains the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n^{\text {th}}]]></fr:tex> roots of unity. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex> be a generator for the Galois group <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\zeta ]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n^{\text {th}}]]></fr:tex> root of unity. We define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Lagrange Resolvent</html:dfn> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\lambda (\alpha ,\zeta )\in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> by
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\lambda (\alpha ,\zeta ):=\alpha +\zeta \sigma (\alpha )+\zeta ^{2}\sigma ^{2}(\alpha )+…+\zeta ^{n-1}\sigma ^{n-1}(\alpha )]]></fr:tex>
where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ^{k}=\sigma \circ …\circ \sigma ]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex> composed with itself <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex> times.</fr:p>
 
   
